------------------------------------------------------------
1) EAZY template set from Brammer, van Dokkum & Coppi (2008)
These templates reduce the input set of Grazian et al.
(2006) templates to a subset of 5 "principal component"
templates following the Blanton & Roweis (2007) algorithm. 
An additional template is added to the 5 principal
components to account for dusty galaxies that don't appear
in semi-analyitic models. These should be use in
"TEMPLATE_COMBOS a" mode.
------------------------------------------------------------
EAZY_v1.0/
eazy_v1.0.spectra.param


------------------------------------------------------------
2) Blanton & Roweis (2007).  Included in the BR07 directory are
the templates taken directly from their paper, and also versions
extended into the mid-IR using Bruzual & Charlot (2003) models
with exactly the parameters used in the BR07 paper.  The spectra.param
files use these extended templates by default.
------------------------------------------------------------
BR07/
br07_default.spectra.param
br07_goods.spectra.param


------------------------------------------------------------
3) Coleman, Wu & Weedman (1980) + Kinney et al. (1996),
extended by Arnouts et al.
(http://www.oamp.fr/people/arnouts/LE_PHARE/)
------------------------------------------------------------
CWW+KIN/
cww+kin.spectra.param


------------------------------------------------------------
4) Grid of single Pegase templates designed to match the 
set described by Grazian et al. (2006).  "Pegase13" 
contains the set of Constant-SFR models with additional
dust reddening following the Calzetti (2000) law.  These
should be used with "TEMPLATE_COMBOS 1" mode.
------------------------------------------------------------
PEGASE2.0/
pegase.spectra.param
pegase13.spectra.param


